When submitting programming exercises, please make sure to do the following or points will be deducted:

Name the file using this format - YourName_ProgrammingExericse_#.py - you must do this so I don't have issues when putting your files in PyCharm for me to test. 
All code should be in functions. 
Put line spacing between sections of code. 
Comment your code and please put comments above your lines of code (not after). Your comments should explain why the code is doing something. 
Please use proper grammar, spelling and punctuation when prompting and displaying to users. 
All programming exercises will be accompanied by a word document file to resemble a technical design document.
In the technical design document, add a screenshot of your output from running your code. There should be no errors in your output. Any errors should be fixed before submitting. Click here Download here
 for an example. 
All programming exercises should be in your repository along with the technical design document. Upload the technical design document manually to your repository. 
